  "description": "Someone was asking about how to arrange a container garden with beans, corn, sunflowers, and squash. I said:\nI would do beans on the north and squash on the south (the squash leaves shade the ground on the southern side, corn shades the north side and beans\u0026rsquo;ll find their own way better than squash can. I think you could probably do 6-8 beans on the north side, then 2 rows of 12-14 corn each (I plant corn tight compared to most folk and never have problems), then 5-6 squash on the south side. I\u0026rsquo;d do sunflowers on the west side to give it all some afternoon shade.\n",
  "name": "2025-08-12, Arranging a container garden",
